```python
def find_original_set(*args):
    original_set = set()

    for arg in args:
        original_set.update(arg)

    return original_set
```
Note: The code assumes that each argument is a set of distinct integers, as stated in the specification. If any of the arguments have duplicates within themselves, those duplicates will be removed when the argument is added to the original_set.
